mate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"During a maintenance window, it is sometimes necessary to have the CLC and CC enabled  for various reasons, but not want to allow users to make calls to the API that would change the cloud configuration, start/stop instances, etc. Disabling network access to the host running these services is not always feasible because that would interrupt other communication to the host that is wanted. This is especially true in the case of the CC and CLC on the same host, and communication to the NCs from the CC is needed to verify a maintenance operation before allowing access to the clouds users.\r\n\r\nIdeally this would be something an administrator could easily turn on/off during maintenance or while troubleshooting a critical service issue to help isolate variables. ","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":"PRD-39","customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/version/10602","id":"10602","description":"Eucalyptus 3.3.0","name":"3.3.0","archived":false,"released":true,"releaseDate":"2013-06-18"}],"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"Option to disable access to API during maintenance window ","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=wjimenez","name":"wjimenez","key":"wjimenez","accountId":"557058:aeaf1802-955b-4912-babe-257f2c73182d","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/4627f87801fc89de81042f7d76b4f9a3?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/4627f87801fc89de81042f7d76b4f9a3?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/4627f87801fc89de81042f7d76b4f9a3?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyp